cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper is about face recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and incorporates attributes such as gender and ethnicity into the training process. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function to regularize the feature mapping, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of RGB-D data and the focus on accuracy and robustness could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, since the paper deals with face recognition, it could also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
